00:00:04.250 --> 00:00:07.140
It’s hard to find a modern movie that doesn’t
flaunt it’s CGI in your face.

00:00:07.140 --> 00:00:12.040
And while that’s not necessarily a bad thing,
audiences come to assume that the medium is

00:00:12.040 --> 00:00:15.350
used strictly for monsters, explosions, and
superpowers.

00:00:15.350 --> 00:00:19.860
And while that might be true to an extent,
there are a lot more instances of subtle manipulation

00:00:19.860 --> 00:00:21.090
than you might realize.

00:00:21.090 --> 00:00:25.620
A little softening here, a little lens flare
there, and suddenly the whole movie is completely

00:00:25.620 --> 00:00:26.620
different.

